        <abstract>
            <p>Discusses possibility of publishing a sketch of his views.</p> 
<p>Comments on CL’s letter [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">1862</hi>].</p> 
            <p>Mentions various geological topics.</p>
            <p>Asks to borrow publication by Heer.</p> 
<p>Mentions flight of <hi rend="italic">Colymbetes</hi> over ocean.</p> 
            <p>Recalls visit by Wollaston.</p>
            <p>Notes views of Hooker and Huxley on species.</p>
            <p>Mentions ability of ducks to transport plant seeds.</p>
        </abstract>
